1 WHEREAS, Devoy was a devoted and loving father, grandfather, son, nephew,
2 cousin, and friend, exemplifying the true meaning of each of these roles throughout his life;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, Devoy was preceded in death by his grandparents, Alma and Marcellus
5 Copper Sr.; his aunt, Thelma Copper; and his uncles, Marcellus Copper Jr. and Henry
6 Copper; and
7 WHEREAS, he leaves to cherish his memory his loving mother, Sylvia Copper; his
8 daughter, Dasianay Copper; his son, Devoy Copper Jr.; his granddaughter, Journei Copper;
9 his uncle, Dale Copper Sr.; and a host of other relatives and friends; and
10 WHEREAS, the memory of Devoy Colbert Copper Sr. shall live forever in the minds
11 and hearts of all who knew and loved him.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
13 does hereby express sincere and heartfelt condolences upon the passing of Devoy Colbert
14 Copper Sr.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
16 Devoy Colbert Copper Sr.'s mother, Sylvia Copper.
